üìò WEEK 3 ‚Äì DAY 2 JavaScript | Functions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üéØ Goal of Day 9

‚úî Understand **what functions are**
‚úî Learn **different types of functions**
‚úî Use **parameters, return values**
‚úî Write **reusable & clean JavaScript code**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß† What is a Function?

A **function** is a **block of reusable code** that performs a specific task.

üìå Instead of writing the same code again and again, we use functions.

---

üßæ Basic Function Syntax

```js
function greet() {
  console.log("Hello World");
}

greet(); // function call
```

Parts of a Function

* `function` ‚Üí keyword
* `greet` ‚Üí function name
* `{}` ‚Üí function body
* `greet()` ‚Üí calling the function

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì• Function with Parameters

Parameters allow passing data to functions.

```js
function greet(name) {
  console.log("Hello " + name);
}

greet("Saakshi");
```

üìå `name` ‚Üí parameter
üìå `"Saakshi"` ‚Üí argument

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì§ Function with Return Value

Functions can return data.

```js
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}

let result = add(5, 3);
console.log(result);
```

üìå `return` sends value back

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üßÆ Default Parameters

Used when no argument is passed.

```js
function greet(name = "User") {
  console.log("Hello " + name);
}

greet(); // Hello User
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÅ Function Expressions

Function stored in a variable.

```js
const greet = function () {
  console.log("Hello");
};

greet();
```

üìå Useful in callbacks

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ö° Arrow Functions (Modern JS)

```js
const greet = () => {
  console.log("Hello Arrow Function");
};
```

Arrow Function with Return

```js
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
```

üìå Shorter & cleaner syntax
üìå Widely used in modern JS

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÑ Callback Functions

A **callback** is a function passed as an argument.

```js
function showMessage(callback) {
  callback();
}

showMessage(function () {
  console.log("Callback executed");
});
```

üìå Used in:

* Events
* Timers
* APIs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚è±Ô∏è Anonymous Functions

Functions without a name.

```js
setTimeout(function () {
  console.log("Executed after 2 seconds");
}, 2000);
```
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© Scope in Functions

Local Scope

```js
function test() {
  let x = 10;
}
```

üìå `x` not accessible outside

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Global Scope

```js
let y = 20;

function show() {
  console.log(y);
}
```

üìå Global variables accessible everywhere

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÅ Nested Functions

Functions inside functions.

```js
function outer() {
  function inner() {
    console.log("Inner function");
  }
  inner();
}

outer();
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ùå Common Beginner Mistakes

* Forgetting to call function
* Missing `return`
* Confusing parameters & arguments
* Overusing global variables

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üí° Best Practices

* Use meaningful function names
* Keep functions small
* Use arrow functions when possible
* Avoid global variables
* Reuse functions

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úÖ DAY-2 Summary (Week-3)

* What functions are
* Function syntax
* Parameters & return
* Arrow functions
* Callback functions
* Scope & best practices
